The paper discusses the resiliency of Massive MIMO systems to Inter-Symbol Interference (ISI) when diversity combining techniques are used at the Base Station (BS). This topic falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of Angle-of-Arrival (AoA) information and the Equal Gain Combiner (EGC) receiver, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses simulations to validate the findings, which is relevant to the Communications (cs.COM) sub-category.
